Fort Collins ColoradoanUpdate: Monday afternoon, JBS announced the Greeley facility would remain closed through April 24.
After dozens of employees tested positive and at least two have died from the new coronavirus, Colorado's governor announced Greeley's JBS meat packaging plant will remain closed indefinitely.
A public health order issued Friday required the Weld County plant to close immediately through April 15 to meet specific requirements outlined by the state and county health departments.
